{
  "title": "Automated multi branch publishing based on Jenkins",
  "type": "lab",
  "description": "This article talks about creating a single pipeline to publish different branches to different environments based on the `go-hello-world` project. Developers commit to code repositories and Jenkins automatically triggers the pipeline which then deploys to different environments based on the branches. The `Generic Webhook Trigger` plugin is used to automatically fetch branches. Tools such as Kubernetes, docker, and helm are used. Different namespaces are created in Kubernetes for each environment such as development, test, co-location, etc. Furthermore, repositories are created on Harbor to allow images of each environment to be pushed to different repositories.",
